snippet.title: 🇬🇪🇦🇺Have you tasted AMBER WINE....or ZIBIBBO? Georgia v Australia!! | [B2-P2] | Battle of the Wines
snippet.description:
Which global winemaker will triumph?  Georgia v Australia?  Lado or Brad?  Discover the best wine competition in the world in Battle of the Wines and learn about wine and winemaking at the same time.  Meet some great wine personalities, with blind tasting by the judges in exotic locations.  These judges are a mixture of wine experts, passionate wine enthusiasts and entry-level drinkers........."WineyPeople".

This "Battle" is in our "Skin Contact" group, one of 16 categories that will be decided as we work towards category and a single competition winner - with over 300 of the best wines from all over the globe participating.

In this "Battle", the "Nominators" are leading Australian wine writer Katie Spain and the winemaker himself Lado Uzunashvili from Georgia.

Battle of the Wines took its initial inspiration from a 1224 poem La Bataille des Vins (Battle of the Wines) by 13th century Norman poet Henry d’Andeli. It tells the story of the first famous wine competition organised by the French King Philip Augustus, which drew over 70 wine samples mostly from northern and central France but some from as far away as Spain and Cyprus.  Probably to the surprise of many, a sweet Cypriot wine widely believed to be an antecedent of modern Commandaria wines was the winner.

Let's see what surprise results emerge as the competition progresses!

Insta: https:  battleofthewines
Facebook:  @battlewines

👉 Discover the next competitors in "Battle" 3: Australia v France!!
